  "title": "万圣节前夜的谋杀",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\126-万圣节前夜的谋杀-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 37,
  "summary": "At the Canterbury Stone Circle in November, a man leads Miranda to a stone carved with a double axe. He discusses the necessity of sacrifice to create beauty and offers her a golden goblet filled with a peach-flavored liquid, instructing her to drink so she will always be happy. As Miranda prepares to drink, Nicholas Lanser intervenes, pulling her away from the man and a knife. Lanser informs Miranda that there is no sacrifice ceremony and reveals that a missing exchange student was actually found dead in a well. He identifies the man who brought Miranda to the circle as the person responsible for that girl's death.\n\nIn a subsequent meeting with Poirot, the Chief Constable, and other officials, Miranda is questioned about what she witnessed nearly two years prior. She explains that she previously saw a man and a woman carrying a body in the quarry garden. At the time, she observed blood on a scarf and a knife, though she initially believed it was an accident. She later witnessed the same pair in March, shortly after Easter, discussing a Greek island and a signed agreement. Miranda identifies the two individuals as Mrs. Drecker and Michael. She admits she did not report the incident at the time because Michael had convinced her that the act was a necessary ritual sacrifice.",
